    "summary": "Consultant for unlocking heritage collections in the cultural and natural history sector. Advising from my expertise and love for our history and photographic technology. Sharing with you how to get all that historically relevant information digitally available by digitisation and online publication for research, education and public use. Through crowd-sourcing, AI enrichment, industrial digitisation, collection websites, open data and smart search technology. Assisting with collection preparation, public engagement, application of standards, barcoding, logistics and on-site projects. We look for partnerships and collaboration: your knowledge of the collections combined with our state-of-art and personal services will lead to amazing results.\n\nExperienced in various European research and development projects to shift the boundaries forward in what is possible with the analogue collections held everywhere in the world.\n\nPragmatic, efficient, keen, don't waste time. Love to give advice, help you make the most of it! Lasting relationships are my goal, working together into the future. Trying to distribute the good stuff that we have available, from our high-end services to our continuous technological developments. Leading to our high-quality, scale-able, predictable and most economic solutions. Aiming to let the heritage community profit from our developments. \n\nGet in touch and Unlock that Heritage!",
